page.title: 19BIRDS IN THE AREA
page.content: Along the old Railway Banks the habitat provides an ideal location for numerous species of birds. The rearing of Partridge and Pheasants has been established at the eastern end of the line. Two feeding stations have also been set up. Breeding birds include Blue,Great and Coal Tit,Blackbirds,Song and Mistle Thrush,Robin,Wren,Goldfinch and Chaffinch. Summer visitors include Blackcap,Chiff Chaff,Willow warbler,Pied and Spotted Flycatcher. Winter roosts for Starlings and Corn Buntings have also been located. The surrounding farmland supports Skylarks,Yellowhammer,Cornbunting and Linnet.Large numbers of Wood Pigeon can be found. Kestrels,Sparrowhawk,Barn,Tawny and Little Owl hunt over this area.
